selectComponents()

selectComponents(mixed $startY, int $startM, int $startD, int $endY,  $endM,  $endD, mixed $cType, bool $flat, bool $any, bool $split) : array

select components from calendar on date or selectOption basis

Ensure DTSTART is set for every component. No date controls occurs.

Parameters

mixed $startY

optional, start Year, default current Year ALT. array selecOptions ( *[ => ] )
int $startM

optional, start Month, default current Month
int $startD

optional, start Day, default current Day
int $endY

optional, end Day, default $startD
$endM
$endD
mixed $cType

optional, calendar component type(-s), default FALSE=all else string/array type(-s)
bool $flat

optional, FALSE (default) => output : array[Year][Month][Day][]

                           TRUE            => output : array[] (ignores split)
bool $any

optional, TRUE (default) - select component(-s) that occurs within period

                           FALSE          - only component(-s) that starts within period
bool $split

optional, TRUE (default) - one component copy every DAY it occurs during the

                                            period (implies flat=FALSE)
                           FALSE          - one occurance of component only in output array

Returns

array —

or FALSE

Tags

author

Kjell-Inge Gustafsson, kigkonsult ical@kigkonsult.se
since 2.11.22
  • 2012-02-13

sort()

sort( $sortArg) : void

sort iCal compoments

ascending sort on properties (if exist) x-current-dtstart, dtstart, x-current-dtend, dtend, x-current-due, due, duration, created, dtstamp, uid if called without arguments, otherwise sorting on specific (argument) property values
